<http://www.isid.org>
See Also
Bluetongue, sheep - Spain (Balearic Islands) (02) 20001127.2062
Bluetongue, sheep - Spain (Balearic Islands): OIE report 20001125.2055
Date: 8 Dec 2000
From: Chris Groit <griot@freesurf.ch>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE)

OIE Follow-up report No. 1 (See also: 13 Oct 2000)
--------------------------------------------------
Extracts from the monthly animal disease reports of Spain for Oct and Nov
2000 and a fax received on 7 Dec 2000 from Dr. Quintiliano Perez Bonilla,
Director General of Animal Production, Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries
and Food, Madrid:
End of previous report period: 11 Oct 2000 (see Disease Information, 13
[40, 181, dated 13 Oct 2000).
End of this report period: 30 Nov 2000.
Total number of new outbreaks during the month:
Oct 2000: 118
Nov 2000: 166
Location of the outbreaks: islands of Majorca and Minorca.
Total number of susceptible animals in the outbreaks:
month / susceptible animals / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
Oct 2000 / 14 248 / 1407 / 549 / 858 / 0
Nov 2000 / 16 605* / 850 / 338 / 512 / 0
*(ovine, bovine, caprine)
